Christine Lillico, 47, from Heddon-on-the-Wall, Northumberland, was trusted with looking after her dying parents' bank accounts .
But instead of using the money to care for their dying parents, she plundered their life savings to bankroll her own lifestyle .
By the time her fraud was discovered she had stolen a total of £78,000 .
She was jailed for 20 months and ordered to pay her brother John Air junior £39,000 - which would have been his inheritance .